## Agent knowledge base

All detailed knowledge for authoring analytics notebooks lives in `agent-core/`
(canonical) with a mirror under `.github/agents/` (legacy copies, kept for
backward compatibility). The entry points are:

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `agent-core/rules/core-rules.md` | Non-negotiable behavioural rules — always apply |
| `agent-core/catalog/knowledge-index.yaml` | Index of all reference files, runbooks, and recipes with keywords and join caveats |
| `agent-core/catalog/tables/` | Per-table YAML manifests with join rules and validators |
| `agent-core/references/` | Per-table schemas: `ani.md`, `apr.md`, `orgdb.md`, `source.md`, `scival.md`, `sdg.md`, `patents.md`, `ads-derived/`, `library.md` |
| `agent-core/runbooks/` | Step-by-step procedures: `databricks.md`, `local-python.md`, `aws-and-s3.md` |
| `agent-core/recipes/` | Copy-paste notebook templates for common analysis patterns |
| `agent-core/roles/` | Portable subagent role definitions |
| `agent-core/profiles/` | Client and user preference profiles |
| `tools/qa/validate_notebook.py` | Static notebook quality checker |
| `scripts/validate_agent_core.py` | Validate all catalog references are intact |
| `scripts/init_project.py` | Bootstrap a new project scaffold |
| `scripts/closeout_project.py` | Finalize a project session |

For analytics tasks, invoke the **analyst** agent (`.github/agents/analyst.agent.md`).
The analyst reads `core-rules.md` and `knowledge-index.yaml` at the start of
every conversation, then consults the relevant reference files and recipes as needed.

For project lifecycle, invoke the **project-resources** agent
(`.github/agents/project-resources.agent.md`).

For agent maintenance — teaching new facts, consolidating lessons,
promoting corrections — invoke the **agent-trainer** agent
(`.github/agents/agent-trainer.agent.md`). Route recurring corrections
through `agent-improvement/` rather than directly editing generated
instructions.
